Sentencas: This study aims at optimization of major processing parameters of combustion CVD for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrode fabrication.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD

Sentencas: A series of depositions were performed to reveal the correlation between process parameters and the microstructures observed as well as the interfacial resistances between electrodes and electrolytes.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD

Sentencas: It is found that deposition temperature has a significant impact on electrode morphology as well as interfacial resistance.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD

Sentencas: Deposition temperatures lower than 1000 degreesC resulted in cathodes with very high interfacial resistances while temperatures higher than 1400 degreesC led to over-densification.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD

Sentencas: Thus for deposition of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) - Sm0.1Ce0.90O2-delta (SDC) composite cathodes on Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) electrolyte, the performance is optimized at deposition temperatures between 1200 and 1300 degreesC. Cathodes of 25-40 mum thick can be deposited onto GDC pellets in 5 - 10 min using a 0.05 M precursor solution.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD

Sentencas: The interfacial polarization resistances between SSC-SDC electrode and YSZ electrolyte were two orders of magnitude higher than those between the electrode and GDC electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication of Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-δ-Sm0.1Ce0.9O2-δ cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells using combustion CVD
